sierdzio's bin scripts - an useful collection of bash scripts.

Distributed under GNU GPLv3 license.

Those currently include:
 - a                    - synonym for git add .
 - archive              - packs the file/ folder given as ${1} into an tar.bz2 archive, adds current date to it's name
 - assistant            - launches Qt Assistant from default location (this script is broken, but can be fixed)
 - automount            - a stub for easy mounting drives
 - autoumount           - a stub for easy unmounting (not needed too much)
 - c                    - a synonym for git commit
 - dcrawrecursive       - runs dcraw -T recursively on every file in folders below and including current one
 - dist-upgrade         - runs a repo update and distribution upgrade (apt-get)
 - fuck                 - displays a fortune cookie when you are desperate enough to curse on terminal
 - grep_error           - greps for errors (old script, needs review)
 - s                    - synonym for git status
 - updateQmlTo2.0       - updates all files below current folder from Qml 1.0 to 2.0
 - upgrade              - performs a repo update and system upgrade
